  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean energy for clean water supply</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will scale up and extend the solar powered piped water scheme in Chiwashira dam in Gokwe North, in order to guarantee all year round improved access to water for multiple uses in the target communities. Provision of infrastructure will be accompanied by training on management and maintenance. 
150 households, comprising 390 women and girls and 360 men and boys will have access to clean water through the installation of slow sand filters.
This will result in improved living conditions and increased resilience to climate change through sustainable access to clean water using renewable energy sources.</narrative>
  </description>
